claim.claim-text:
1. A machine readable storage device embodying a program of machine-readable instructions executable by a digital processing apparatus to create at least one volume in a disk storage system, wherein the instructions are executed to perform operations, the operations comprising:
receiving a request to create at least one volume on the disk storage system indicating a volume size and number of the at least one volume to create, wherein volumes represent storage entities;
selecting a storage pool object representing one of a plurality of storage pools having available storage space from which to create the requested number of at least one volume, wherein the storage pools have available storage space to assign to create volumes;
retrieving a storage configuration service of the disk storage system using an association of a disk storage system object representing the disk storage system and the selected storage pool object;
associating the disk storage system object representing the disk storage system with the retrieved storage configuration service;
setting a volume size of the at least one volume to create to a calculated size;
setting the storage pool as the selected storage pool object; and
invoking a method through the retrieved storage configuration service for each volume in the requested number of at least one volume to create.

6. The machine readable storage device of claim 1, wherein the operations further comprise:
determining if an error has occurred;
recording the error in response to determining that the error occurred;
selecting an additional storage pool object identifying one storage pool with available space to create the at least one volume in response to determining that an additional storage pool object identifying a storage spool with available space is available;
repeating the operations of retrieving, associating, setting the storage pool, and the invoking operations using the selected additional storage pool object as the selected storage pool object.

8. A computing system in communication with a disk storage system, comprising:
a memory; and
a processing device coupled to the memory, wherein the processing device is programmed to perform operations for creating at least one volume in the disk storage system, the operations comprising:
receiving a request to create at least one volume on the disk storage system, wherein the request specifies a volume size and a requested number of the at least one volume, wherein volumes represent storage entities;
selecting a storage pool object representing one of a plurality of storage pools having available storage space from which to create the requested number of at least one volume, wherein the storage pools have available storage space to assign to create volumes;
retrieving a storage configuration service of the disk storage system using an association of a disk storage system object representing the disk storage system and the selected storage pool object;
associating the disk storage system object representing the disk storage system with the retrieved storage configuration service;
setting a volume size of the at least one volume to create to a calculated size;
setting the storage pool as the selected storage pool object; and
invoking a method through the retrieved storage configuration service for each volume in the requested number of at least one volume to create.

13. The computing system of claim 8, wherein the operations further comprise:
determining if an error has occurred;
recording the error in response to determining that the error occurred;
selecting an additional storage pool object identifying one storage pool with available space to create the at least one volume in response to determining that an additional storage pool object identifying a storage spool with available space is available;
repeating the operations of retrieving, associating, setting the storage pool, and the invoking operations using the selected additional storage pool object as the selected storage pool object.

15. A method for creating at least one volume in a disk storage system, comprising:
receiving a request to create at least one volume on the disk storage system indicating a volume size and number of the at least one volume to create, wherein volumes represent storage entities;
selecting a storage pool object representing one of a plurality of storage pools having available storage space from which to create the requested number of at least one volume, wherein the storage pools have available storage space to assign to create volumes;
retrieving a storage configuration service of the disk storage system using an association of a disk storage system object representing the disk storage system and the selected storage pool object;
associating the disk storage system object representing the disk storage system with the retrieved storage configuration service;
setting a volume size of the at least one volume to create to a calculated size;
setting the storage pool as the selected storage pool object; and
invoking a method through the retrieved storage configuration service for each volume in the requested number of at least one volume to create.

20. The method of claim 15, further comprising:
determining if an error has occurred;
recording the error in response to determining that the error occurred;
selecting an additional storage pool object identifying one storage pool with available space to create the at least one volume in response to determining that an additional storage pool object identifying a storage spool with available space is available;
repeating the operations of retrieving, associating, setting the storage pool, and the invoking operations using the selected additional storage pool object as the selected storage pool object.
